FBIS3-1398 "drafr059_c_94019" FBIS-AFR-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA 600 Armed Men Attack Commuters on Train From Pretoria MB2803071494 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 0600 GMT 28 Mar 94 MB2803071494 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Language: Afrikaans Article Type:BFN [Text] Six hundred people armed with automatic weapons, assegais, and knobsticks last night attacked and robbed passengers on a train en route from Pretoria to Johannesburg. The attack took place at Oakmore Station northeast of Johannesburg. Police confiscated at least three AK-47 rifles and four pistols when the train was searched at Birchley Station. No arrests have yet been made.
